iStore recently announced that Apple-authorised iPhone screen replacements would be available in South Africa from 29 January. Authorised screen repairs use a genuine Apple replacement screen, ensuring that full functionality and the manufacturer’s warranty are retained. The company has advised customers against repairing their devices using organisations which are not authorised service providers. “Only Apple Authorised Service Providers have access to genuine Apple Spare Parts, and Apple proprietary equipment to perform an authorised screen replacement,” it said. The following companies are not Apple Authorised Service Providers, said iStore: